args: So what DO I like? Goodness, this is\nturning out to be as hard as I feared\nit might be.
I know I've asked before, but what was it\nthat you all enjoy again?
Painting, reading, eating... Hmm.\nNone of those sound like they're for me.
Perhaps if you were to try those activities\nout for yourself, you might see what's so\nenjoyable about them.
Hmm. Do you think you'd be willing to try\nthem with me?
In that case, let's begin with painting.
Portraiture is a bit advanced, so we'll start\nby painting something easy, like an apple.
An apple sounds lovely. Let's do it!
Well, I feel like mine came out quite well.\nHow about you, Louise?
Hmm. She must really be in the zone.\nLet's just take a look at her work here...
Oh, hello, Cleo. Are you already done with\nyour painting? I didn't notice.
Might I see how yours came out?
No! Absolutely not! No one is allowed to\nsee it—ESPECIALLY not you!
Er, but we've been painting side-by-side\nall this time. Why the change of heart?
The design? The sense of perspective?\nThe shading? It's all PERFECT! How in the\nworld did you manage this?
Oh, I used to paint with Lowen from time\nto time.
It made him happy for us to paint together,\nso I did it a lot when he was little.
Well, it's an enormous waste for such a\nrich talent to sit unused!
Promise me that you will keep painting—\nAND that you'll teach me all your secrets!
This needs to stay between us, Louise,\nbut the kind of books I like...are THESE.
Is this a romance novel? I don't know that\nI've ever seen one before.
Hmm, let me see what this is about...\nAhem! ＂Princess! My love for you is true!＂
＂The different places we occupy in the\nworld are but trivialities before the power\nof this love! You shall be mine forever!＂
So this is a romance novel, huh?
Y-you're so good at reading stories...\nSomething about your tone just sets\nmy heart racing!
Oh? Then perhaps I should read this one to\nyou as well. Let's see...
＂I will never give up! I will pursue you to\nthe very ends of the world itself!＂
STAAAAAWP! My heart is going to tear\nfree of my chest if you continue!
P-please give me time to recover before\nyou read another line! I beg it of you!
Oh, but promise that you'll read whatever\nbook I pick out for you. PROMISE ME!
Um, all right? I'm just going to...slowly\nback out of the room now. Farewell.
Here ya go, Louise! This should be all the\nfood what we ordered.
Oh, and it's my treat, so feel free to\neat up and chow down!
Oh man, this grub is REALLY turnin' my\ncrank today. What's the deal?!
Ah yes, that's what your body is craving.\nLooks like my order was right on the mark.
Wait, yer sayin' ya ordered stuff based\nspecifically on what ya thought my body\nneeded?
Indeed. I was always quite careful about\nLowen's nutrition so he'd grow up healthy.\nForce of habit now, I suppose.
No matter who it is, I want people to eat\nthe food their body needs.
Aw, thanks, Louise! I could eat this stuff\nall day!
R-Ranzal, no! Overeating is still terrible\nfor you!
Uuuurgh... Ate too much...\nStomach bloated... Tongue swollen...\nFeet...black? Oh man, that ain't good...
I warned you not to overeat.
Excuse me, miss? We're, um, out of food\nnow, so I'm going to just close the shop.\nIf you wouldn't mind settling up...?
Yes, my companion will... Ranzal?\nRanzal, wait! You have to pay the check!
Get over here at once, Ranzal!\nYou must pay for all the food you ate!
BRAAAAAP! Oh yeah, that's the stuff.\nNow I'm gonna take me a nap...
*sigh* I'm very sorry about this.\nPlease allow me to pay for him.
What's wrong, Louise? You look beat.
I suppose I am a little worn out.
Did you manage to find your new hobby?
Actually, that is the source of my troubles.
There you are, Louise! I have that book\nI want you to read, as well as my favorite\nlistening pillow.
Louise! Wait! I need you to explain the\nconcept of parallax distance in landscape\nwatercolors!
Yo, Louise! Let's grab a bite to eat!\nMy belly must FEEEED!
I'm pleased that everyone is counting\non me now, but I...
Well, I feel as if I've relapsed right back\ninto being someone's older sister!
I still have no idea what MY likes are.
Heh. The mountain of self-discovery is a\nsteep one sometimes.
